        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 14 at 6:46PM MDT until June 14 at 7:15PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 646 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hobson, or 20
miles west of Lewistown, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Hobson, Moore, Ackley Lake State Park, Glengarry, and Moccasin.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
